<p><b>John Royce "Johnny" Mathis</b> (born September 30, 1935,<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href="Gilmer,_Texas" title="Gilmer, Texas">Gilmer, Texas</a>, United States) is an American singer of <a href="Popular_music" title="Popular music">popular music</a>. Starting his career with singles of <a href="Standard_(music)" title="Standard (music)">standard music</a>, he became highly popular as an album artist, with several dozen of his albums achieving gold or platinum status, and 73 making the <a href="Billboard_charts" title="Billboard charts">Billboard charts</a> and Guinness World Record music chart historian <a href="Paul_Gambaccini" title="Paul Gambaccini">Paul Gambaccini</a>, confirms "Johnny Mathis has sold well over 350 million records worldwide".</p>
<p>One of the last and most popular in a line of traditional male vocalists who emerged before the rock-dominated 1960s, Johnny Mathis concentrated on the romantic side of <a href="Jazz" title="Jazz">jazz</a> and <a href="Pop_music" title="Pop music">pop music</a> standards for the <a href="Adult_contemporary" title="Adult contemporary" class="mw-redirect">adult contemporary</a> audience of the 1960s and 1970s. Mathis later made it big in the market for <a href="Music_album" title="Music album" class="mw-redirect">music albums</a>, where a dozen of his LPs hit gold or platinum. While he concentrated on theme-oriented albums of show tunes and traditional favorites during the 1960s, he began incorporating <a href="Soft_rock" title="Soft rock">soft rock</a> by the 1970s and remained a popular concert attraction well into the 1990s.</p>
<p>Unsurprisingly, given his emphasis on long sustained <a href="Music_notes" title="Music notes" class="mw-redirect">notes</a> and heavy <a href="Vibrato" title="Vibrato">vibrato</a>, Mathis studied with an opera coach prior to his teenage years, and he was nearly lured into the opera singing profession.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
